🚀 Features
🔍 Smart Data Comparison
Compare two datasets using custom key columns
Detect:
Added records
Missing records
Modified values

🧮 Intelligent Data Normalization
Automatic handling of:
Dates (standardized format)
Numeric values (tolerance-based comparison)
Text (case-insensitive, trimmed)

⚖️ Tolerance-Based Numeric Matching
Avoid false mismatches due to rounding differences
Configurable tolerance level

🧩 Flexible Column Control
Select key columns for matching
Ignore irrelevant columns during comparison

🧠 Smart Matching Mode
Handles duplicate records using advanced matching logic
Performs second-pass reconciliation for better accuracy

📊 Detailed Comparison Output
Status classification:
same
different
only_in_file1
only_in_file2
Displays exact columns with differences

🖥️ User-Friendly GUI
Built with Tkinter
File selection, column selection, preview, and export in one interface
📤 Export Results
Export comparison results to Excel for reporting and auditing

🛠️ Tech Stack
Python
Pandas
Tkinter (GUI)

📂 Use Case

This tool is especially useful for:

Data validation between daily reports
QA checks for ETL pipelines
Financial data reconciliation
Comparing system exports (before vs after)
Detecting discrepancies in large datasets

